 Project:ICS 

 
 

 
 Watch a brief overview  of Project:ICS, and check out   our  YouTube page  for other   videos about Project:ICS. 
 
 Project:ICS is comprised of upper division classes designed to give our students real-world experience specifying, designing, constructing, testing and documenting complete projects in partnership with local companies, University offices and non-profit organizations. 
 This program and the courses associated with it compliment the computer science curriculum by providing students an opportunity to experience an assignment motivated by industry needs and constrained by business demands. 
 »  Read the program FAQ  
 »  Watch customer and student testimonials about Project:ICS  
 »  View sample student projects  
 » To be considered for this program or for further information please contact Kristin Huerth at  khuerth@ics.uci.edu  or (949) 824-3074. 
  PROGRAM BENEFITS 
  Work closely with a team of highly qualified, motivated students and faculty 
 Direct contact with Bren School students improves recruiting efforts 
 Strengthen or build a close relationship between your company and the Bren School 
 Recognition as a funding partner of the Bren School 
